The new CI failure (check_mondo_obsoletes) has been fixed in commit 6209faf.
  The issue was that the CI check downloads a fresh MONDO mirror and validates
  that all deprecated MONDO terms in EFO's import list have their replacement 
  terms also imported. Two pre-existing MONDO terms became deprecated in the  
  current MONDO version:                                                      
                                                                              
  • MONDO_0012017 (obsolete Parkes Weber syndrome) → now replaced by          
  MONDO_0700325 (Parkes Weber syndrome)                                       
  • MONDO_0700044 (obsolete TUBB2A-related tubulinopathy) → now replaced by   
  MONDO_0014337 (TUBB2A-related complex cortical dysplasia)                   
                                                                              
  The fix adds both replacement IRIs to iri_dependencies/mondo_terms.txt and  
  imports/mondo_terms.txt. The CI will regenerate mondo_import.owl from the   
  updated terms list.

